---
export const prerender = true;
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Fedify on Netlify</title>
    <style>
      :root { color-scheme: light dark; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }
      main { margin: 12vh auto; max-width: 44rem; padding: 0 1.5rem; }
      h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 4rem); line-height: 1; }
      code { background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent); padding: .2em .4em; }
      li { margin-block: .8rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Fedify on Netlify</h1>
      <p>
        This Astro application serves an ActivityPub actor through Netlify
        Functions and processes outgoing jobs with Netlify Async Workloads.
      </p>
      <p>Follow <code>@netlify@{Astro.url.host}</code> from the fediverse.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Actor state and ordering sequences use Netlify Database.</li>
        <li>Fedify queue messages use durable Async Workloads events.</li>
        <li>This page remains prerendered; federation routes run on demand.</li>
      </ul>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
